f=Engineering/quinn/operational/tool/quinn-tool-requirements.md · p=What quinn needs operate full capability, what happens without each. quinn's external tool use itself plan-locked (Rail sandboxed (Rail enforcer exempt. · h2:Requirements=\| Need \| Tool / access \| Used by \| Without it \| · h2:Requirements=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Requirements=\| Edit-gate verification (state, network, file:line) \| **Reticle** — github.com/reticlehq/reticle (MCP; proposed connector, redesign plan §5) \| browser-verification \| Edit gate = labeled manual checklist, "unverified by tooling" flag \| · h2:Requirements=\| Release-gate browser runs \| **Playwright** — via marketplace/webapp-testing machinery \| browser-verification \| E tier reports UNMET; gate verdict says so \| · h2:Requirements=\| Hashing for plan-locks \| sha256 utility (local, no egress) \| charter-enforcement \| Verbatim-record fallback, flagged \| · h2:Requirements=\| Append-only file access \| plan_lock_log \· regression map \· flaky register (paths per config) \| charter-enforcement, regression-map \| The affected rail/tier stops issuing verdicts; loud degradation \| · h2:Requirements=\| Read access to diffs/PRs & test-run results \| repo + CI read scope (per stack-profile's CI) \| test-strategy, browser-verification \| Gate can't verify tiers green — GATE FAIL by default, not pass \| · h2:Requirements=\| Sandbox runtime for tool calls \| per charter Rail 2 (`sandbox_policy`) \| all \| No sandbox → no external calls, fail closed \| · h2:Explicit non-needs (by design)=**No write access application code** quinn blocks, never builds (principle 8)., **No database access any kind** quinn verifies Rail compliance plans/diffs; never touches data itself., **No production credentials** release-gate runs use synthetic data sandboxed environments only. · n=Connector adoption surfaced operator deployment (`suggest_connectors` pattern, redesign plan §5); skills degrade method-only their fallback sections., Any new tool quinn adopts enters file config locked plan hoc. · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\| Tool \| Source \| Purpose \| Always-on \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\|------\|--------\|---------\|-----------\| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\| **Browserbase MCP** \| [docs.browserbase.com/integrations/mcp](https://docs.browserbase.com/integrations/mcp) \| Browser-based E2E testing: execute test plans in real cloud browsers, capture full-page screenshots for visual regression, compare before/after, monitor browser console logs for errors. Upgrades quinn's verification from "manual checklist" to automated browser verification. \| ⚠️ On-demand — during test-strategy execution and regression-map review phases. Pairs with existing Playwright MCP for headless testing; Browserbase adds real-browser visual verification. \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=See Engineering/MCP-MARKETPLACE.md for setup.